alertMessageArguments.description: Concatenated set of strings representing the message arguments of the event. batteryTableEntry.name: batteryTableEntry
batteryTableEntry.description: An entry in the battery table. A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.

batteryNumber.name: batteryNumber
batteryNumber.description: Instance number of this battery entry.

batteryState.name: batteryState
batteryState.description: Current state of battery. Possible values: 1: The current state could not be determined. 2: The battery is operating normally. 3: The battery has failed and needs to be replaced. 4: The battery temperature is high or charge level is depleting. 5: The battery is missing or not detected. 6: The battery is undergoing the re-charge phase. 7: The battery voltage or charge level is below the threshold.

batteryComponentStatus.name: batteryComponentStatus
batteryComponentStatus.description: The status of the battery itself without the propagation of any contained component status. Possible values: 1: Other 2: Unknown 3: OK 4: Non-critical 5: Critical 6: Non-recoverable

batteryPredictedCapacity.name: batteryPredictedCapacity
batteryPredictedCapacity.description: This entry is obsolete. Use the batteryComponentStatus or batteryState instead.

batteryFQDD.name: batteryFQDD
batteryFQDD.description: The battery's Fully Qualified Device Descriptor (FQDD) as represented in Storage Management.

batteryDisplayName.name: batteryDisplayName
batteryDisplayName.description: The battery's friendly FQDD as represented in Storage Management.

controllerNumber.name: controllerNumber
controllerNumber.description: Instance number of this controller entry.

controllerName.name: controllerName
controllerName.description: The controller's name as represented in Storage Management.

controllerRebuildRate.name: controllerRebuildRate
controllerRebuildRate.description: The rebuild rate is the percentage of the controller's resources dedicated to rebuilding a failed disk when a rebuild is necessary.

controllerCacheSizeInMB.name: controllerCacheSizeInMB
controllerCacheSizeInMB.description: The controller's current amount of cache memory in megabytes.

controllerRollUpStatus.name: controllerRollUpStatus
controllerRollUpStatus.description: Severity of the controller state. This is the combined status of the controller and its components. Possible values: 1: Other. 2: Unknown. 3: OK 4: Non-critical 5: Critical. 6: Non-recoverable.

controllerComponentStatus.name: controllerComponentStatus
controllerComponentStatus.description: The status of the controller itself without the propagation of any contained component status. Possible values: 1: Other 2: Unknown 3: OK 4: Non-critical 5: Critical 6: Non-recoverable

controllerDriverVersion.name: controllerDriverVersion
controllerDriverVersion.description: Currently installed driver version for this controller on the host.

controllerPCISlot.name: controllerPCISlot
controllerPCISlot.description: The PCI slot on the server where the controller is seated. This data is not reported for embedded or integrated controllers,

controllerReconstructRate.name: controllerReconstructRate
controllerReconstructRate.description: The reconstruct rate is the percentage of the controller's resources dedicated to reconstructing a disk group after adding a physical disk or changing the RAID level of a virtual disk residing on the disk group.

controllerPatrolReadRate.name: controllerPatrolReadRate
controllerPatrolReadRate.description: The patrol read rate is the percentage of the controller's resources dedicated to perform a patrol read on disks participating in a virtual disk or hot spares.

controllerBGIRate.name: controllerBGIRate
controllerBGIRate.description: The background initialization (BGI) rate is the percentage of the controller's resources dedicated to performing the background initialization of a redundant virtual disk after it is created.

controllerCheckConsistencyRate.name: controllerCheckConsistencyRate
controllerCheckConsistencyRate.description: The check consistency rate is the percentage of the controller's resources dedicated to performing a check consistency on a redundant virtual disk.

controllerPatrolReadMode.name: controllerPatrolReadMode
controllerPatrolReadMode.description: Identifies the patrol read mode setting for the controller. Possible values: 1: Not one of the following or could not be determined. 2: Not Supported on this controller. 3: Disabled. 4: Automatic. 5: Manual.

controllerPatrolReadState.name: controllerPatrolReadState
controllerPatrolReadState.description: This property displays the current state of the patrol read process. Possible values: 1: Not one of the following or could not be determined. 2: Patrol read is not running. 3: Patrol read is running.

controllerPersistentHotSpare.name: controllerPersistentHotSpare
controllerPersistentHotSpare.description: Indicates whether hot spare drives would be restored on insertion into the same slot.

controllerSpinDownUnconfiguredDrives.name: controllerSpinDownUnconfiguredDrives
controllerSpinDownUnconfiguredDrives.description: Indicates whether un-configured drives would be put in power save mode by the controller.

controllerSpinDownHotSpareDrives.name: controllerSpinDownHotSpareDrives
controllerSpinDownHotSpareDrives.description: Indicates whether hot spare drives would be put in power save mode by the controller.

controllerSpinDownTimeInterval.name: controllerSpinDownTimeInterval
controllerSpinDownTimeInterval.description: The duration in minutes after which, the unconfigured or hot spare drives will be spun down to power save mode.

controllerPreservedCache.name: controllerPreservedCache
controllerPreservedCache.description: Indicates whether preserved cache or pinned cache is present on the controller.

controllerCheckConsistencyMode.name: controllerCheckConsistencyMode
controllerCheckConsistencyMode.description: The current check consistency mode setting for the controller. Possible values: 1: Not one of the following. 2: Not supported on this controller. 3: Normal check consistency operation. 4: Check consistency operation will stop on encountering an error.

controllerCopyBackMode.name: controllerCopyBackMode
controllerCopyBackMode.description: The current copy back mode setting for the controller. Possible values: 1: Not one of the following. 2: Not supported on this controller. 3: Disks assigned as spares could revert back to spare status. 4: Data from physical disk participating in a virtual disk could be automatically copied to the assigned hot spare in case former has a predictive failure event. 5: Copyback mode is disabled.

controllerSecurityStatus.name: controllerSecurityStatus
controllerSecurityStatus.description: The controller's current security/encryption status.. Possible values: 1: The current status could not be determined. 2: Controller is not operating in an encryption mode. 3: Controller is operating in the Local Key Management (LKM) encryption mode.

controllerEncryptionKeyPresent.name: controllerEncryptionKeyPresent
controllerEncryptionKeyPresent.description: Indicates whether encryption key is assigned for the controller.

controllerEncryptionCapability.name: controllerEncryptionCapability
controllerEncryptionCapability.description: The type of encryption supported by the controller. Possible values: 1: Not one of the following. 2: No encryption supported, 3: Local Key Management,

controllerLoadBalanceSetting.name: controllerLoadBalanceSetting
controllerLoadBalanceSetting.description: The ability of the controller to automatically use both controller ports (or connectors) connected to the same enclosure in order to route I/O requests. Possible values: 1: Not one of the following. 2: Not supported. 3: Automatic load balancing is active. 4: Load balancing is inactive.

controllerMaxCapSpeed.name: controllerMaxCapSpeed
controllerMaxCapSpeed.description: The maximum speed of the controller.in Gigbits per second (Gbps). Possible values: 1: The speed could not be determined. 2. 1.5 Gbps 3: 3.0 Gbps 4: 6.0 Gbps 5: 12.0 Gbps

controllerSASAddress.name: controllerSASAddress
controllerSASAddress.description: The SAS address of the controller.

controllerFQDD.name: controllerFQDD
controllerFQDD.description: The controller's Fully Qualified Device Descriptor (FQDD) as represented in Storage Management.

controllerDisplayName.name: controllerDisplayName
controllerDisplayName.description: The controller's friendly FQDD as represented in Storage Management.

controllerT10PICapability.name: controllerT10PICapability
controllerT10PICapability.description: Indicates whether the controller supports the T10 PI (Protection Information). These protection fields are known as DIF (Data Integrity Fields). Possible values: 1: Not one of the following. 2: Capable of supporting T10 PI. 3: Not capable of supporting T10 PI.

controllerRAID10UnevenSpansSupported.name: controllerRAID10UnevenSpansSupported
controllerRAID10UnevenSpansSupported.description: Indicates whether uneven spans for RAID 10 virtual disk is supported on the controller.

controllerEnhancedAutoImportForeignConfi.name: controllerEnhancedAutoImportForeignConfigMode
controllerEnhancedAutoImportForeignConfi.description: Indicates the status of enhanced auto-import of foreign configuration property of the controller. 1: Not one of the following. 2: Not Supported. 3: Disabled. 4: Enabled.

controllerBootModeSupported.name: controllerBootModeSupported
controllerBootModeSupported.description: Indicates whether headless boot mode settings are supported on the controller.

controllerBootMode.name: controllerBootMode
controllerBootMode.description: Indicates the boot mode of the controller. Possible values: 1: Not applicable for this controller. 2: User mode: User interaction required for all boot messages (not applicable for uEFI environments). 3: Continue Boot On Error. User interaction only required for critical messages. 4: Headless Mode Continue On Error. User interaction is not required. Controller boot may halt on Error. 5: Headless Safe Mode. Controller shall boot to safe mode on critical errors.

physicalDiskTable.name: physicalDiskTable
physicalDiskTable.description: A table of managed physical disks. The number of entries is related to number of physical Disks discovered in the system. The maximum number of entries is implementation dependent. Note: The properties in this table may not be applicable to all entries.

physicalDiskTableEntry.name: physicalDiskTableEntry
physicalDiskTableEntry.description: An entry in the physical Disk table. A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.

physicalDiskNumber.name: physicalDiskNumber
physicalDiskNumber.description: Instance number of this physical disk entry.

physicalDiskName.name: physicalDiskName
physicalDiskName.description: The physical disk's name as represented in Storage Management.

physicalDiskManufacturer.name: physicalDiskManufacturer
physicalDiskManufacturer.description: The name of the physical disk's manufacturer.

physicalDiskState.name: physicalDiskState
physicalDiskState.description: The current state of this physical disk. Possible states: 1: The current state could not be determined. 2: The physical disk is available for use, but no RAID configuration has been assigned. 3: A RAID configuration has been assigned to the physical disk. 4: The physical disk has been moved from another controller and contains all or some portion of a virtual disk. 5: The physical disk is not available to the RAID controller. 6: The physical disk is currently blocked by controller. 7: The physical disk is not operational. 8: The physical disk is not a RAID capable disk 9: The physical disk has been removed. 10:The physical disk media has been placed in read only mode.

physicalDiskProductID.name: physicalDiskProductID
physicalDiskProductID.description: The model number of the physical disk.

physicalDiskSerialNo.name: physicalDiskSerialNo
physicalDiskSerialNo.description: The physical disk's unique identification number from the manufacturer.

physicalDiskRevision.name: physicalDiskRevision
physicalDiskRevision.description: The firmware version of the physical disk.

physicalDiskCapacityInMB.name: physicalDiskCapacityInMB
physicalDiskCapacityInMB.description: The size of the physical disk in megabytes.

physicalDiskUsedSpaceInMB.name: physicalDiskUsedSpaceInMB
physicalDiskUsedSpaceInMB.description: The amount of used space in megabytes on the physical disk. This is not applicable for NVMe devices.

physicalDiskFreeSpaceInMB.name: physicalDiskFreeSpaceInMB
physicalDiskFreeSpaceInMB.description: The amount of free space in megabytes on the physical disk. This is not applicable for NVMe devices.

physicalDiskBusType.name: physicalDiskBusType
physicalDiskBusType.description: The bus type of the physical disk. Possible values: 1: The bus type could not be determined. 2: Small Computer System Interface (SCSI). 3: Serial Attached SCSI (SAS). 4: Serial Advanced Technology Attachment (SATA). 5: Fibre channel. 6: PCIe.

physicalDiskSpareState.name: physicalDiskSpareState
physicalDiskSpareState.description: The status of the disk as a spare. Possible values: 1: Physical disk is not a spare. 2: Physical disk is a dedicated hot spare. 3: Physical disk is a global hot spare.

physicalDiskComponentStatus.name: physicalDiskComponentStatus
physicalDiskComponentStatus.description: The status of the physical disk itself without the propagation of any contained component status. Possible values: 1: Other 2: Unknown 3: OK 4: Non-critical 5: Critical 6: Non-recoverable

physicalDiskPartNumber.name: physicalDiskPartNumber
physicalDiskPartNumber.description: The part number of the disk.

physicalDiskSASAddress.name: physicalDiskSASAddress
physicalDiskSASAddress.description: The SAS address of the physical disk.

physicalDiskNegotiatedSpeed.name: physicalDiskNegotiatedSpeed
physicalDiskNegotiatedSpeed.description: The data transfer speed that the disk negotiated while spinning up in Gigbits per second (Gbps). Possible values: 1: The speed could not be determined. 2. 1.5 Gbps 3: 3.0 Gbps 4: 6.0 Gbps 5: 12.0 Gbps 6: 5 GT/s (applicable for NVMe devices). 7: 8 GT/s (applicable for NVMe devices).

physicalDiskCapableSpeed.name: physicalDiskCapableSpeed
physicalDiskCapableSpeed.description: The maximum data transfer speed supported by the disk in Gigbits per second (Gbps). Possible values: 1: The speed could not be determined. 2. 1.5 Gbps 3: 3.0 Gbps 4: 6.0 Gbps 5: 12.0 Gbps 6: 5 GT/s (applicable for NVMe devices). 7: 8 GT/s (applicable for NVMe devices).

physicalDiskSmartAlertIndication.name: physicalDiskSmartAlertIndication
physicalDiskSmartAlertIndication.description: Indicates whether the physical disk has received a predictive failure alert.

physicalDiskManufactureDay.name: physicalDiskManufactureDay
physicalDiskManufactureDay.description: The day of the week (1=Sunday thru 7=Saturday) on which the physical disk was manufactured.

physicalDiskManufactureWeek.name: physicalDiskManufactureWeek
physicalDiskManufactureWeek.description: The week (1 thru 53) in which the physical disk was manufactured.

physicalDiskManufactureYear.name: physicalDiskManufactureYear
physicalDiskManufactureYear.description: The four digit year in which the physical disk was manufactured.

physicalDiskMediaType.name: physicalDiskMediaType
physicalDiskMediaType.description: The media type of the physical disk. Possible Values: 1: The media type could not be determined. 2: Hard Disk Drive (HDD). 3: Solid State Device (SSD).

physicalDiskPowerState.name: physicalDiskPowerState
physicalDiskPowerState.description: The power state of the physical disk. Possible Values: 1: Not one of the following. 2: The physical disk is in the spun up state. 3: The physical disk is in the spun down state. 4: The physical disk is changing from spun down state to spun up state or vice versa. 5: The Solid State Device (SSD) is powered on.

physicalDiskRemainingRatedWriteEndurance.name: physicalDiskRemainingRatedWriteEndurance
physicalDiskRemainingRatedWriteEndurance.description: This property is applicable to SSD media type only. This indicates the wear-out percentage of the SSD. Typically it is a value between 0 to 100. However, if the value is not available or not applicable (in the case of HDD media type) the value will be 255.

physicalDiskOperationalState.name: physicalDiskOperationalState
physicalDiskOperationalState.description: The state of the physical disk when there are progressive operations ongoing. Possible values: 1: There is no active operation running. 2: Data from a redundant virtual disk is currently being rebuilt onto the physical disk. 3: Data on the disk is being erased. 4: Data is being copied from a hot spare disk to the physical disk or vice versa.

physicalDiskProgress.name: physicalDiskProgress
physicalDiskProgress.description: The progress percentage of the operation that is being performed on the physical disk. This is applicable only if there is a progressive operations ongoing

physicalDiskSecurityStatus.name: physicalDiskSecurityStatus
physicalDiskSecurityStatus.description: The security/encryption status of the physical disk. Possible Values: 1: The physical disk supports encryption. 2: The physical disk does not support encryption 3: The physical disk is encrypted. 4: The physical disk is locked by a key. 5: The physical disk is locked by a foreign key.

physicalDiskFormFactor.name: physicalDiskFormFactor
physicalDiskFormFactor.description: The form factor of the physical disk. Possible values: 1: The form factor could not be determined. 2: 1.8 inch. 3: 2.5 inch. 4: 3.5 inch.

physicalDiskFQDD.name: physicalDiskFQDD
physicalDiskFQDD.description: The physical disk's Fully Qualified Device Descriptor (FQDD) as represented in Storage Management.

physicalDiskDisplayName.name: physicalDiskDisplayName
physicalDiskDisplayName.description: The physical disk's friendly FQDD as represented in Storage Management.

physicalDiskT10PICapability.name: physicalDiskT10PICapability
physicalDiskT10PICapability.description: Indicates whether the physical disk supports the T10 PI (Protection Information). These protection fields are known as DIF (Data Integrity Fields). Possible values: 1: Not one of the following. 2: Capable of supporting T10 PI. 3: Not capable of supporting T10 PI.

physicalDiskBlockSizeInBytes.name: physicalDiskBlockSizeInBytes
physicalDiskBlockSizeInBytes.description: The block size (in bytes) of the physical disk. This is not applicable for NVMe devices. Possible values: 1: 512. 2: 4096

physicalDiskProtocolVersion.name: physicalDiskProtocolVersion
physicalDiskProtocolVersion.description: Applicable for NVMe devices only. The NVMe protocol version supported by the device.

physicalDiskPCIeNegotiatedLinkWidth.name: physicalDiskPCIeNegotiatedLinkWidth
physicalDiskPCIeNegotiatedLinkWidth.description: Applicable for NVMe devices only. The PCIe link width negotiated with the host during device initialization.

physicalDiskPCIeCapableLinkWidth.name: physicalDiskPCIeCapableLinkWidth
physicalDiskPCIeCapableLinkWidth.description: Applicable for NVMe devices only. The PCIe link widths the device is capable of supporting.

virtualDiskTable.name: virtualDiskTable
virtualDiskTable.description: A table of managed virtual disks. The number of entries is related to number of virtual disks discovered in the system. The maximum number of entries is implementation dependent. Note: The properties in this table may not be applicable to all entries.

virtualDiskTableEntry.name: virtualDiskTableEntry
virtualDiskTableEntry.description: An entry in the virtual disk table. A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.

virtualDiskNumber.name: virtualDiskNumber
virtualDiskNumber.description: Instance number of this virtual disk entry.

virtualDiskName.name: virtualDiskName
virtualDiskName.description: The virtual disk's label as entered by the user.

virtualDiskState.name: virtualDiskState
virtualDiskState.description: The current state of this virtual disk (which includes any member physical disks.) Possible states: 1: The current state could not be determined. 2: The virtual disk is operating normally or optimally. 3: The virtual disk has encountered a failure. The data on disk is lost or is about to be lost. 4: The virtual disk encounterd a failure with one or all of the constituent redundant physical disks. The data on the virtual disk might no longer be fault tolerant.

virtualDiskSizeInMB.name: virtualDiskSizeInMB
virtualDiskSizeInMB.description: The size of the virtual disk in megabytes.

virtualDiskWritePolicy.name: virtualDiskWritePolicy
virtualDiskWritePolicy.description: The write policy used by the controller for write operations on this virtual disk. Possible values: 1: Write Through. 2: Write Back. 3: Force Write Back.

virtualDiskReadPolicy.name: virtualDiskReadPolicy
virtualDiskReadPolicy.description: The read policy used by the controller for read operations on this virtual disk. Possible values: 1: No Read Ahead. 2: Read Ahead. 3: Adaptive Read Ahead.

virtualDiskLayout.name: virtualDiskLayout
virtualDiskLayout.description: The virtual disk's RAID type. Possible values: 1: Not one of the following 2: RAID-0 3: RAID-1 4: RAID-5 5: RAID-6 6: RAID-10 7: RAID-50 8: RAID-60 9: Concatenated RAID 1 10: Concatenated RAID 5

virtualDiskStripeSize.name: virtualDiskStripeSize
virtualDiskStripeSize.description: The stripe size of this virtual disk. Possible values: 1: Not one of the following 2: Default. 3: 512 bytes 4: 1 kB, 5: 2 kB, 6: 4 kB, 7: 8 kB, 8: 16 kB, 9: 32 kB, 10: 64 kB, 11: 128 kB, 12: 256 kB, 13: 512 kB, 14: 1 MB, 15: 2 MB, 16: 4 MB, 17: 8 MB, 18: 16 MB

virtualDiskComponentStatus.name: virtualDiskComponentStatus
virtualDiskComponentStatus.description: The status of the virtual disk itself without the propagation of any contained component status. Possible values: 1: Other. 2: Unknown. 3: OK. 4: Non-critical . 5: Critical. 6: Non-recoverable.

virtualDiskBadBlocksDetected.name: virtualDiskBadBlocksDetected
virtualDiskBadBlocksDetected.description: Indicates whether the virtual disk has bad blocks.

virtualDiskSecured.name: virtualDiskSecured
virtualDiskSecured.description: Indicates whether the virtual disk is secured or not.

virtualDiskIsCacheCade.name: virtualDiskIsCacheCade
virtualDiskIsCacheCade.description: Indicates whether the virtual disk is being used as a secondary cache by the controller.

virtualDiskDiskCachePolicy.name: virtualDiskDiskCachePolicy
virtualDiskDiskCachePolicy.description: The cache policy of the physical disks that are part of this virtual disk Possible values: 1: Enabled. 2: Disabled. 3: Default.

virtualDiskOperationalState.name: virtualDiskOperationalState
virtualDiskOperationalState.description: The state of the virtual disk when there are progressive operations ongoing. Possible values: 1: There is no active operation running. 2: The virtual disk configuration has changed. The physical disks included in the virtual disk are being modified to support the new configuration. 3: A Consistency Check (CC) is being performed on the virtual disk. 4: The virtual disk is being initialized. 5: BackGround Initialization (BGI) is being performed on the virtual disk.

virtualDiskProgress.name: virtualDiskProgress
virtualDiskProgress.description: The progress percentage of the operation that is being performed on the virtual disk. This is applicable only if there is a progressive operations ongoing

virtualDiskAvailableProtocols.name: virtualDiskAvailableProtocols
virtualDiskAvailableProtocols.description: List of protocols support by physical disks part of this virtual disk. For e.g. SAS for Serial Attached SCSI or SATA for Serial Advanced Technology Attachment.

virtualDiskMediaType.name: virtualDiskMediaType
virtualDiskMediaType.description: List of media types of the physical disks part of this virtual disk. For e.g. HDD for Hard Disk Drive or SSD for Solid State Device.

virtualDiskRemainingRedundancy.name: virtualDiskRemainingRedundancy
virtualDiskRemainingRedundancy.description: The number of physical disks which can be lost before the virtual disk loses its redundancy.

virtualDiskFQDD.name: virtualDiskFQDD
virtualDiskFQDD.description: The virtual disk's Fully Qualified Device Descriptor (FQDD) as represented in Storage Management.

virtualDiskDisplayName.name: virtualDiskDisplayName
virtualDiskDisplayName.description: The virtual disk's friendly FQDD as represented in Storage Management.

virtualDiskT10PIStatus.name: virtualDiskT10PIStatus
virtualDiskT10PIStatus.description: Indicates whether the virtual disk supports the T10 PI (Protection Information). These protection fields are known as DIF (Data Integrity Fields). Possible values: 1: Not one of the following. 2: Enabled. 3: Disabled.

virtualDiskBlockSizeInBytes.name: virtualDiskBlockSizeInBytes
virtualDiskBlockSizeInBytes.description: The block size (in bytes) of the physical disk part of the virtual disk. Possible values: 1: 512. 2: 4096

enclosureTable.name: enclosureTable
enclosureTable.description: A table of managed enclosures/backplanes. The number of entries is related to number of internal backplane(s) discovered in the system and external storage enclosure(s) attached to the system.. The maximum number of entries is implementation dependent. Note: The properties in this table may not be applicable to all entries.

enclosureTableEntry.name: enclosureTableEntry
enclosureTableEntry.description: An entry in the enclosure table. A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.

enclosureName.name: enclosureName
enclosureName.description: The enclosure/backplane's name as represented in Storage Management.

enclosureState.name: enclosureState
enclosureState.description: The current state of this enclosure/backplane. Possible states: 1: The current state could not be determined. 2: The enclosure is operating normally. 3: The enclosure has encountered a hardware problem or is not responding. 4: The enclosure is no longer connected to the controller or there exists a problem communicating to the enclosure. 5: The enclosure is unstable.

enclosureServiceTag.name: enclosureServiceTag
enclosureServiceTag.description: Enclosure identification used when consulting customer support.

enclosureAssetTag.name: enclosureAssetTag
enclosureAssetTag.description: The asset tag information for the enclosure.

enclosureConnectedPort.name: enclosureConnectedPort
enclosureConnectedPort.description: The port on the controller to which the storage enclosure is connected.

enclosureRollUpStatus.name: enclosureRollUpStatus
enclosureRollUpStatus.description: Severity of the enclosure/backplane state. This is the combined status of the enclosure and its sub-components. Possible values: 1: Other. 2: Unknown. 3: OK. 4: Non-critical. 5: Critical. 6: Non-recoverable.

enclosureComponentStatus.name: enclosureComponentStatus
enclosureComponentStatus.description: The status of the enclosure/backplane.itself without the propagation of any contained component status. Possible values: 1: Other. 2: Unknown. 3: OK. 4: Non-critical . 5: Critical. 6: Non-recoverable.

enclosureFirmwareVersion.name: enclosureFirmwareVersion
enclosureFirmwareVersion.description: The firmware information for the enclosure/backplane.

enclosureSASAddress.name: enclosureSASAddress
enclosureSASAddress.description: The SAS address of the enclosure/backplane.

enclosureDriveCount.name: enclosureDriveCount
enclosureDriveCount.description: The number of disks present in the enclosure/backplane.

enclosureTotalSlots.name: enclosureTotalSlots
enclosureTotalSlots.description: The total physical drive slots in a storage enclosure or server backplane.

enclosureFanCount.name: enclosureFanCount
enclosureFanCount.description: The number of fans present in the storage enclosure.

enclosurePSUCount.name: enclosurePSUCount
enclosurePSUCount.description: The number of Power Supply Units (PSU) present in the storage enclosure.

enclosureEMMCount.name: enclosureEMMCount
enclosureEMMCount.description: The number of Enclosure Management Modules (EMM) present in the storage enclosure.

enclosureTempProbeCount.name: enclosureTempProbeCount
enclosureTempProbeCount.description: The number of temperature sensing devices present in the storage enclosure.

enclosureRedundantPath.name: enclosureRedundantPath
enclosureRedundantPath.description: Indicates whether the controller has multiply paths to reach the storage enclosure.

enclosurePosition.name: enclosurePosition
enclosurePosition.description: The possition of the storage enclosure within a daisy chain.

enclosureBackplaneBayID.name: enclosureBackplaneBayID
enclosureBackplaneBayID.description: The unique bay ID of the backplane.

enclosureFQDD.name: enclosureFQDD
enclosureFQDD.description: The enclosure/backplane's Fully Qualified Device Descriptor (FQDD) as represented in Storage Management.

enclosureDisplayName.name: enclosureDisplayName
enclosureDisplayName.description: The enclosure/backplane's friendly FQDD as represented in Storage Management.

enclosureType.name: enclosureType
enclosureType.description: The protocol supported by the backplane. Possible states: 1: Not one of the following or could not be determined. 2: Not applicable (i.e. object is not a backplane). 3: Supports SAS/SATA. 4: Supports PCIe. 5: Both SAS/SATA and PCIe.

enclosureManagementModuleTable.name: enclosureManagementModuleTable
enclosureManagementModuleTable.description: A table of managed Enclosure Management Modules (EMM) in the external storage enclosure(s). The number of entries is related to number of enclosure management modules discovered in the enclosure(s). The maximum number of entries is implementation dependent. Note: The properties in this table may not be applicable to all entries.

enclosureManagementModuleTableEntry.name: enclosureManagementModuleTableEntry
enclosureManagementModuleTableEntry.description: An entry in the enclosure management module table. A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.

enclosureManagementModuleNumber.name: enclosureManagementModuleNumber
enclosureManagementModuleNumber.description: Instance number of this enclosure management module.

enclosureManagementModuleName.name: enclosureManagementModuleName
enclosureManagementModuleName.description: The enclosure management module's name as represented in Storage Management.

enclosureManagementModuleState.name: enclosureManagementModuleState
enclosureManagementModuleState.description: The current state of this enclosure management module. Possible states: 1: The current state could not be determined. 2: The enclosure management module is operating normally. 3: The enclosure management module has encountered a hardware problem or is not responding. 4: The enclosure management module is no longer connected to the enclosure or there exists a problem communicating to it. 5: The enclosure management module is unstable.

enclosureManagementModulePartNumber.name: enclosureManagementModulePartNumber
enclosureManagementModulePartNumber.description: The part number of the enclosure management module.

enclosureManagementModuleFWVersion.name: enclosureManagementModuleFWVersion
enclosureManagementModuleFWVersion.description: Firmware version of the enclosure management module.

enclosureManagementModuleComponentStatus.name: enclosureManagementModuleComponentStatus
enclosureManagementModuleComponentStatus.description: The status of the enclosure management module.itself without the propagation of any contained component status. Possible values: 1: Other. 2: Unknown. 3: OK. 4: Non-critical . 5: Critical. 6: Non-recoverable.

enclosureManagementModuleFQDD.name: enclosureManagementModuleFQDD
enclosureManagementModuleFQDD.description: The enclosure management module's Fully Qualified Device Descriptor (FQDD) as represented in Storage Management.

enclosureManagementModuleDisplayName.name: enclosureManagementModuleDisplayName
enclosureManagementModuleDisplayName.description: The enclosure management module's friendly FQDD as represented in Storage Management.

enclosureFanTable.name: enclosureFanTable
enclosureFanTable.description: A table of managed fans in the external storage enclosure(s). The number of entries is related to number of fans discovered in the enclosure(s). The maximum number of entries is implementation dependent. Note: The properties in this table may not be applicable to all entries.

enclosureFanTableEntry.name: enclosureFanTableEntry
enclosureFanTableEntry.description: An entry in the fan table. A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.

enclosureFanName.name: enclosureFanName
enclosureFanName.description: The fan's name as represented in Storage Management.

enclosureFanState.name: enclosureFanState
enclosureFanState.description: The current state of this fan. Possible states: 1: The current state could not be determined. 2: The fan is operating normally. 3: The fan has encountered a hardware problem or is not responding. 4: The fan is no longer connected to the enclosure or there exists a problem communicating to it. 5: The fan is unstable.

enclosureFanSpeed.name: enclosureFanSpeed
enclosureFanSpeed.description: Indicates the current relative speed of the fan.

enclosureFanComponentStatus.name: enclosureFanComponentStatus
enclosureFanComponentStatus.description: The status of the fan itself without the propagation of any contained component status. Possible values: 1: Other. 2: Unknown. 3: OK. 4: Non-critical . 5: Critical. 6: Non-recoverable.

enclosureFanFQDD.name: enclosureFanFQDD
enclosureFanFQDD.description: The fan's Fully Qualified Device Descriptor (FQDD) as represented in Storage Management.

enclosureFanDisplayName.name: enclosureFanDisplayName
enclosureFanDisplayName.description: The fan's friendly FQDD as represented in Storage Management.

enclosurePowerSupplyTable.name: enclosurePowerSupplyTable
enclosurePowerSupplyTable.description: A table of managed Power Supply Units(PSU) in the external storage enclosure(s). The number of entries is related to number of power supply unit(s) discovered in the enclosure(s). The maximum number of entries is implementation dependent. Note: The properties in this table may not be applicable to all entries.

enclosurePowerSupplyTableEntry.name: enclosurePowerSupplyTableEntry
enclosurePowerSupplyTableEntry.description: An entry in the power supply unit table. A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.

enclosurePowerSupplyNumber.name: enclosurePowerSupplyNumber
enclosurePowerSupplyNumber.description: Instance number of this power supply unit.

enclosurePowerSupplyName.name: enclosurePowerSupplyName
enclosurePowerSupplyName.description: The power supply unit's name as represented in Storage Management.

enclosurePowerSupplyState.name: enclosurePowerSupplyState
enclosurePowerSupplyState.description: The current state of this power supply unit. Possible states: 1: The current state could not be determined. 2: The power supply unit is operating normally. 3: The power supply unit has encountered a hardware problem or is not responding. 4: The power supply unit is no longer connected to the enclosure or there exists a problem communicating to it. 5: The power supply unit is unstable.

enclosurePowerSupplyPartNumber.name: enclosurePowerSupplyPartNumber
